list.name: Default
list.comment:
New Developer Dependencies: CoffeeScript - A Compile-to-JS language that provides a lot syntactic sugar with regards to javascript constructs and allows powerful, expressive language while still being supported by browsers by compiling down to js. Also includes class and inheritance support.
INSTALL CoffeeScript USING 'npm install -g coffee-script'
django-static-precompiler - Provides pre-compilation utilities for various languages like SASS and CoffeeScript without any bothersome native dependencies. Necessary to use coffeescript.
settings.py: - Setup architecture for installing coffeescript and django-static-precompiler to work with out static files environment.
widgets.py: - Small cleanups for inconsistencies and odd results
rules.py: - Add basic always_true and always_false predicates that should be expected in a rules environment - Add basic, proper, permissions for viewing and editing personal, medical and insurance information of a user - Did not remove code that is in obsolescence until we are sure those rules/[erms are no longer needed.
views.py: - Rewrite some REST views to properly use new AJAX utilities
base_user.coffee and base_user_classes.coffee: - Reimplement base_user.js in CoffeeScript with a whole new permissions system that is both asynchronous and makes sense. - New JS Authenticator and Revertable Changes based system. - Now is asynchronous using the new processNextTick global provided by utility, making use of setTimeout. This should be replaced. - Many small optimization to jQuery selectors and DOM manipulation
measurements.coffee: - Reimplements measurements.js in coffeescript with small optimizations to caching. - In the process, resolved numerous issues that caused weird bugs in the form.
base.js: - Obsolesced certain registry base actions in favor of the actions added in Utility. Now delegates to registry.utility and registry.utility with attempt to override registry base functions. - registry is now extensible up until after utility is initialized - Add processNextTick - Add stopEventBehavior - Delegate processNextTick, stopEventBehavior and csrf to registry.utility analogs
utility.js: - Add stopEventBehavior which provides IE compliant way to prevent Events from doing their default behavior (like a click on an <a> tag changing location). - Add processNextTick which provides a universal way to have actions be held off until the next possible available tick of the VM. This acts similarly to process.nextTick from node.js. - Add processNextTick to window globals - Override base registry functions (csrf and stopEventBehavior, etc.) and make them aliases for utility functions. - Move 'preventExtensions' call for base registry to after utility is instantiated
templates in general: - Mostly converting any script imports to coffeescript imports if necessary. Must use the 'compile' filter from compile_tags.
bower.json: - Cleanup unused and likely to not be used dependencies - Timesheet, Charts, Chance
README update for coffeescript acknowledgement requirements.txt not includes django-static-precompiler
